FBIS4-64617 "drweu087_q_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-087 Daily Report 4 May 1994 TURKEY Monthly Inflation Rate Nears 25 Percent Monthly Inflation Rate Nears 25 Percent TA0405123694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 GMT 4 May 94 TA0405123694 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Text] The inflation rate for April was announced as 24.7 percent. The annual rate of inflation increased by 107.4 percent since April last year. According to a statement issued by the State Statistics Institute, the consumer prices increased by 24.7 percent and the wholesale prices by 32.8 percent during the month of April. This brings the annual increase in the consumer price index to 107.4 percent and the annual increase in the wholesale price index to 125.3 percent.
